crowdsourced_yara_results.description: Detects a suspicious ELF binary with UPX compression
crowdsourced_yara_results.author: Florian Roth (Nextron Systems)

threat_severity.level_description: Severity MEDIUM because it was considered trojan.

attributes.magic: ELF 32-bit MSB executable, MIPS, MIPS-I version 1 (SYSV), statically linked, no section header

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: The sample is a malicious MIPS32 binary, likely an IoT botnet agent (such as Mirai or Gafgyt). It is packed with UPX (indicated by 'upx.sf.net') and employs self-unpacking routines using sys_mmap, sys_mprotect, and sys_cacheflush to execute its payload in memory. Significant IOCs include strings related to known router exploits ('POST /GponForm/diag_'), HTTP request artifacts ('User-Agent:*', '/cdn-cgi/'), and the use of '/proc/self/exe' for self-referencing, which are consistent with automated exploit scanning and botnet persistence.
